The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Merger of Blow Plast, VIP in 1:1 ratio

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, May 12: Decks have been cleared for the merger of Blow Plast with VIP Industries after the respective boards gave their approval today.

 A share exchange ratio of 1:1 has been fixed for the merger, which is proposed to be effective from April 1. 

 We will achieve optimum utilisation of various infrastructure and service facilities and integrate our management activities, thus achieving reduction and better control of costs, said Dilip Piramal, chairman of VIP Industries. 

 VIP Industries is the luggage manufacturer and Blow Plast is the marketing and distribution arm. 

 The merged entity will emerge as a leader in the global luggage industry, leveraging on innovation and a strong marketing strategy, said Piramal. 

 Post merger, the size of the combined entity will be about Rs 500 crore. 

 VIP Industries reported a total income of Rs 335.12 crore and net profit of Rs 8.78 crore for the financial year ended March 31, 2006. Blow Plast has reported total income of Rs 259.28 crore and net profit of Rs 6.74 crore for the year ended March 31, 2006. The merged entity will have exclusive showrooms and will operate in over 50 countries with manufacturing units in Uttaranchal and Nashik. 

 The proposed share exchange ratio has been based on a valuation exercise conducted PriceWaterhouseCoopers and Chhotalal H Shah and Company. 

 There will be better resource mobilisation and financial consolidation to withstand competition from domestic as well as overseas markets, quot; said Sudhir Jatia, managing director of Blow Plast. 




